## TL;DR

Four reasons bezel beats prong on emerald cut diamond earrings:

1. **The price gap is enormous** — bezel 1ct tw in 14K white gold at [$3,080](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/bezel-set-emerald-cut-diamond-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251746?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) vs. prong 1ct tw at [$5,750](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/emerald-cut-diamond-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-1-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251830?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Same paired diamonds. $2,670 cheaper.
2. **Bezel protects the corners** — emerald cut has flat, exposed corners. Prong earrings leave those corners completely open to daily knocks and snagging.
3. **No prong shadows on the table** — four prongs above a flat emerald table cast shadows across the step facets. Bezel sits at the girdle and leaves the table completely open.
4. **Bezel stays secure** — prong tips bend with time. Bezel is one solid piece of metal around the stone. Nothing to splay, nothing to lose.

