## What Are Emerald Cut Diamond Earrings?

Emerald cut diamond earrings feature the step-cut rectangular diamond — the same stone that anchors the [most elegant engagement rings in the emerald cluster](/emerald-cut-diamond-engagement-rings) — in earring form.

The stone has a large, flat table and long parallel step facets running down its face. It does not sparkle like a round brilliant. It does something more specific: it throws clean, deliberate flashes of light. At ear level, that effect is visible from across a room every time you move.

You can get the emerald cut in four earring formats — studs, inside-out hoops, linear drops, and huggies. Each carries the shape differently.

