## The Total Weight Trap

This is the most expensive misunderstanding in diamond earrings. Read it before you look at a single price.

When a pair of earrings lists "1 ct. tw." — that means one carat total weight. Both earrings combined. Not each.

A pair labeled 1ct tw gives you two stones at 0.5ct each. If you want 1ct per ear, you need 2ct tw. That costs [$13,190](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/emerald-cut-diamond-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-2-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251836?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) — more than double the 1ct tw price.

