The inside-out style wraps emerald cuts along both faces of the hoop. The eternity hoops line them along the front only for a slightly cleaner profile. The Diamond Emerald Hoop alternates the emerald cut with other shapes for a mixed pattern.

If you want the most diamond for the least money in this shape, the inside-out hoop at [3ct tw for $4,995](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/inside-out-emerald-cut-diamond-hoop-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-3-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251167?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the best value in this entire post. Three carats total. On sale. Less money than a 1ct tw prong stud.

> "Hoops are underrated in the emerald cut category. The rectangular stones line up perfectly along the hoop — it looks like the shape was designed for this format. The inside-out style gives you constant presence from every angle. If studs feel too subtle, a hoop changes the entire weight of the piece." — Farzana Hasan, **[Diamond Critics](https://diamondcritics.com/about-farzana/)**

