At this level, the hoop comparison becomes striking. The [5ct tw inside-out hoop at $8,100](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/inside-out-emerald-cut-diamond-hoop-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-5-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251169?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) gives you five carats of emerald cut diamond for $5,090 less than the 2ct tw stud. The stud gives you 2 carats total. The hoop gives you 5. Choose based on the profile you want — not the carat number alone.

If you are buying at this level in stud format, always check the lab grown option on the product page. The savings at 2ct tw are substantial.

---

## Lab Grown Emerald Cut Diamond Earrings

All earrings listed in this post offer lab grown diamond upgrade options. Each product page shows a "+ Lab Grown" toggle.

Lab grown diamonds are chemically and optically identical to natural. In earrings, where you are buying two stones at once, the savings multiply. A pair of lab grown emerald cut studs at a given carat weight typically costs 60–70% less than the natural equivalent.

For earrings specifically, that means you can step up a full size bracket for the same budget. If the [1.5ct tw prong at $9,290](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/emerald-cut-diamond-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-1-1-2-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251833?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is your ceiling, the lab grown version of the [2ct tw pair](https://www.bluenile.com/jewelry/earrings/emerald-cut-diamond-stud-earrings-in-14k-white-gold-2-ct-tw-h-i-si1-si2-item-251836?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) may fall within the same range. Click "+ Lab Grown" on the product page to see the current pricing.

For the full case for lab in step-cut formats, read [Lab Grown Emerald Cut Diamond: Why the Open Table Changes the Equation](/lab-grown-emerald-cut-diamond).

